The paper deals with learning a preference model from a set of examples, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The use of dynamic programming and genetic algorithms for optimization suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The problem of learning from pairwise ordinal preferences can also be seen as a ranking problem, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of algorithms for optimization and decision-making also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of computational economics (cs.CE). Finally, the paper deals with discrete values and pairwise comparisons, which are common topics in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
